---
import BaseLayout from "../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Veterans"
  description="Supporting a veteran who may be struggling with gambling? How to understand the risk and start the conversation — for family, partners, and friends."
>
  <header class="page-header">
    <div class="container">
      <p class="page-header__eyebrow">
        <a href="/family-and-friends">← Family &amp; friends</a>
      </p>
      <h1>Veterans</h1>
      <p class="page-header__lead">
        Supporting a veteran who may be struggling with gambling? Here's how to
        understand the risk and start the conversation — without minimizing
        what they've been through.
      </p>
    </div>
  </header>

  <section class="fnf-top">
    <div class="container fnf-top__grid">
      <div class="fnf-top__main">
        <p>
          Veterans face a higher rate of gambling problems than the general
          population, and the reasons run together. PTSD and traumatic brain
          injury affect the same brain systems gambling targets. Long stretches
          of structure followed by sudden unstructured time create a window
          where harm can take hold. And treatment systems built around
          substance use don't always reach gambling.
        </p>
        <p>
          You don't need to be a clinician to help. The most powerful thing you
          can do is open a calm, respectful conversation — without making it
          about your own fear.
        </p>
      </div>
      <aside class="fnf-top__aside">
        <figure class="fnf-photo">
          <img
            src="/photos/family-and-friends/veterans.jpg"
            alt="A senior couple share a quiet, thoughtful conversation, looking at each other."
            width="800"
            height="600"
            loading="lazy"
          />
        </figure>
      </aside>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="container prose">
      <p>
        More detailed guidance — signs to watch for, how to start the
        conversation, what not to do, VA-aware resources, and how to take care
        of yourself — is being developed for this page. The same framework as
        the <a href="/family-and-friends/youth">Youth</a> page applies; the
        cohort-specific adaptation is in progress.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
